<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68fe46e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s11112"><num value="11112">§ 11112.</num><heading> Master’s lien for wages</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The master of a documented vessel has the same lien against the vessel for the master’s wages and the same priority as any other seaman serving on the vessel.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68fe46f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/99/307/s1/19/B">Pub. L. 99–307, § 1(19)(B)</ref>, <date date="1986-05-19">May 19, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/446">100 Stat. 446</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
